cs.CR, cs.OS, cs.SY, cs.SE, cs.PL

The paper discusses the issue of timing channels and proposes a solution to prevent them in operating systems. This topic falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and operating systems (cs.OS). The paper also presents a design and implementation of the proposed solution in the seL4 microkernel, which relates to system and network architecture (cs.SY) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance overhead of the solution, which is relevant to programming languages (cs.PL).
